{% extends "templates/layout-en-gb.njk" %}
{% set tab = "products" %}

{% block meta %}
    <link rel="canonical" href="https://patryktrajder.com/en-gb/products/super-booster-2000/equipment/"/>
    <title>Accessories | Tube notcher | Patryk Trajder</title>
{% endblock meta %}

{% block vectors %}
    {% include "vectors/arrow-right.sym" %}
    {% include "vectors/home.sym" %}
{% endblock %}

{% block body %}
    <main>
        <article>
            <header class="gap-top">
                <nav class="breadcrumbs">
                    <a href="/en-gb/">
                        <svg class="home icon">
                            <use xlink:href="#icon-home"></use>
                        </svg>
                    </a>
                    <svg class="icon">
                        <use xlink:href="#icon-arrow-right"></use>
                    </svg>
                    <a href="/en-gb/products/">Products</a>
                    <svg class="icon">
                        <use xlink:href="#icon-arrow-right"></use>
                    </svg>
                    <a href="/en-gb/products/super-booster-2000/">Super Booster 2000</a>
                    <svg class="icon">
                        <use xlink:href="#icon-arrow-right"></use>
                    </svg>
                    <a href="/en-gb/products/super-booster-2000/equipment/">
                        <b>Equipment</b>
                    </a>
                </nav>
                <h1>Tube Notcher - Super Booster 2000 - Accessories</h1>
            </header>
            <section class="gap-top">
                <h2>Flat holdfast</h2>
                <p>There is a clamp from&#32;<q>triangles</q>&#32;as standard, with which we can fix both pipes and profiles. However, if we very often want to fix profiles, extending the set with&#32;<q>flat pressure</q>&#32;will be a good solution.</p>
                <div class="row gap-top">
                    <div>
                        <div class="image-loading">
                            <img src="/assets/images/super-booster-2000/equipment/detail1-w1120.jpg" alt="Flat profile pressure"/>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    <div>
                        <p>The flatbed is made up of two elements, which are prepared for assembly by: cut to size, machined edges and a drilled hole. We only have to weld them together.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="row">
                    <div>
                        <div class="image-loading">
                            <img src="/assets/images/super-booster-2000/equipment/detail2-w1120.jpg" alt="example of using a profile clamp">
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    <div>
                        <p>The flatbed is compatible with the screw (it has a mounting hole of the same diameter).</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="row">
                    <div>
                        <div class="image-loading">
                            <img src="/assets/images/super-booster-2000/equipment/detail3-w1120.jpg" alt="example of using a profile clamp">
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    <div>
                        <p>
                            By using a flat pressure plate, we minimize the risk of incorrectly fastened profiles.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="row">
                    <div>
                        <div class="image-loading">
                            <img src="/assets/images/super-booster-2000/equipment/detail4-w1120.jpg" alt="example of using a profile clamp">
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    <div>
                        <p>With a prism, our profile automatically positions itself to the axis.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </section>
        </article>
    </main>
{% endblock %}